calculation with integres
let expression
expr expression
$(( expression))
of 3 the $((...)) method is preferred
all work with following operators
+
-
*
/
%

let is bash internal
let a=1+2
echo $a
let a++
echo$a
expr external command can be used in scripts
 $((...)) allows you to put calculations between parenthesis
 $((2*3))


ADVANCED CALCULATION TOOLS

bc is an advanced calculation tool allows to work with decimals
bc used in pipes: echo "12/5" | bc
to print decimals in result use -l: echo "12/5" | bc -l
bc access to built-in mathematical functions echo "sqrt(1000)" | bc -l
factor decomposes an integer into prime factors factor 399


